title: comfortable but develop an odor
review: these adidas slides are not designed to get wet they are not waterproof nor waterresistant so definitely do not use these when getting out of the shower or around the poolalso these seem to develop and hold onto a foot odor over time i take care of my feet they are relatively clean and i shower daily including briefly cleaning my feet still these developed a foot odor over time even while i had only been wearing these indoors within my houseif you are looking for waterproof slides that can be used insideoutside the shower or around the pool i instead suggest purchasing adilette shower slides or adilette aqua slides both from adidas these are actually waterproofthe water will not soak into any of the materialsand if you are looking for comfortable slidesthe ones that feel like you are walking on cloudsi suggest purchasing adilette comfort slides from adidas these are not as waterproof as the shower or aqua slides but they still seem waterresistant more importantly the footbed is actually very soft and comfortable and most importantly they dont build up and hold onto any foot odors like the adilette boost slides

prod_name: adidas
title: not like the older versions cut my foot
review: i have been wearing these adidas sandals for  years over this time ive had i think  pairs and usually the only reason i buy new ones is because theyve been ruined by a dog or something like that i bought these ones a while back and they were so uncomfortable and different than previous ones that i couldnt bring myself to break them in so i fixed up my old pair and have been wearing them i decided to finally give them another shot i wore them around the house for a few hours and they cut the tops of my toes all of them im not talking blisters im talking bleeding cuts on my skin the underside of the sandal that goes over the foot is not at all soft like my old pairs the material is not the same its thinner and more plasticy and the foot bed is hard also not the cushiony foam i feel like these are counterfeit but they were sold by amazon so i doubt they would sell fake adidas apparel i would definitely not recommend these sandals sorry to say but these are not like the ones ive known loved and trusted over the years i was expecting to have to break them in a little bit but these i cant bear to wear at all perhaps try another seller

prod_name: adidas
title: do not buy for big feet
review: i have size  mens feet i have noticed a trend with largesized slides and thong sandals sandal makers do not know how the foot scales up by that i mean my feet are a couple inches longer than the average males but my ankles while larger are not also a full two inches longer so adidas puts the strap around  the way up the shoe and when the average size  man slides his foot in it stops so his toes sit comfortably the size  slide also puts the strap  up the shoe however i have more foot to slide in before it reaches my ankle so when my foot comes to a stop in these slides my toes hang way over the fix to this would be not to treat larger shoe sizes as carbon copies of the average model and to place the strap further down the shoetwo stars because its a good looking slide and adidas is not the only shoemaker who makes this mistake

title: good little shoes
review: bought these to jog and walk in they are a pretty decent pair of shoes they are lightweight and relatively comfy after you break them in for the first couple weeks they were hard on my heels nothing a couple bandaids or k tape couldnt fix now that they are broken in they are a dream they keep your feet nice and cool for hot runs or hot summer days when youre out walking i think once mine bite the dust i will definitely order again i gave  stars because of the rough beginning and because the sizing is a bit off after reading other reviews and checking out the size chart on the website i decided to order half size up and im glad i did they do fit a bit small

prod_name: under armour
title: lightweight and comfortable
review: i am extremely impressed with the performance of this trainersthe fit is true to size and the cushioning provides excellent support for my feet during long runs the grip on the sole is also exceptional giving me confidence and stability on different terrainswhat i love most about these trainers is how lightweight they are they feel like an extension of my feet allowing me to focus on my stride and pace without feeling weighed down the breathability of the materials is also a standout feature keeping my feet cool and dry even during intense workoutsoverall i highly recommend these running trainers to anyone who is serious about their fitness goals they are stylish comfortable and most importantly provide the performance necessary to push yourself to new heights these trainers have become an essential part of my running routine and i look forward to continuing to use them for many miles to come

prod_name: under armour
title: form fitting shock absorbing foot heaven
review: ive been in the market for new walking shoes for a while now and have tried on at least a dozen pairs before these it was immediately apparent to me that these were the winning pairproslight weight but structurally strongthe heel cup is pronounced holding my foot in place nicely even when unlacedgreat shock absorptionmiddle of the road arch support it neither pushes into my foot nor does it leave my arch floatingthe shoe widens out at the ball of the foot just right to support the sides of my feet without squeezing themconsbasic insole thats comfortable but not as padded or advanced as other shoeslow rise ankle socks are a no no with these shoes as the heel cup i enjoy will suck your sock into the shoe and off your heelall in all for  these are great shoes they dont even feel like youre wearing shoes the wife likes the look and feel so much she made me order her a womans pair of the same shoe you cant go wrong with this shoe

prod_name: the north face unisex vault rucksack
title: heavy backpack but decent for school
review: im a bit biased when it comes to north face products because ive been using their brand for many years so last year i decided to get the north face vault backpack for my son in middle school he liked that it was black and that it had sturdy straps im going to point out the pros and conspros very sturdy and can put  chromebook has its own pocket for laptopschromebooks  books and about  foldersnotebooks yes thats a lot for a middle school but we tested the backpack out putting in as much stuff as possible when we first got it there are  front pockets one is larger than the other my son put his penspencils etc in the smaller pocket the bigger pocket had his earbud case calculator and other small items for his classes there are  side pockets for water bottles the zippers are easy to grasp all around with  separate zipper pulls the straps are thick and there is a strap you can tie around your waist area for more security and supportcons the meshstyle water bottle holders arent very well sewn one of them broke after a month granted you are going to constantly take out and put back your water bottles so i thought the holders should have held up for at least one school year right the backpack itself is pretty heavy with nothing in it so be prepared to carry a very heavy backpack if your childs school doesnt have lockers for them to put their stuff in and they have to carry their books and laptops all dayoverall this backpack held up well enough for about one year and a half i did notice some of the seams on the front pockets become looser but that could just be a user issue the ripped water bottle holders on the side being ripped so easily could have been made with higher quality material or stitchingi think its a nice looking backpack  its not flashy and it has a small north face logo

title: do not like the accessory pocket  second zippered compartment bag does not stand up
review: this backpack is very sturdy but not particularly functional  the main compartment is very good although the laptop padded sleeve is very tight ie best for a  inch laptop tight for a  and impossible for a   i have two main complaints both of which require the return of this product  first the second compartment is not full length and runs only halfway down the pack  as such all your accessories pens cords keys clif bar etc are in the second compartment and this runs only halfway down  when you open the zipper to get at stuff because it is all topweight because it does not go all the way down the second compartment flops down as soon as the zipper is opened  it is annoying as hell and makes getting stuff out difficult  competitor bags including the bag this replaced the under armour hustle have the compartment go all the way down  this prevents the flop when you open the zipper  second major complaint but similar is that the bag will not stand on its own  so when you bring it to your desk or next to your desk it will not stand up  it always wants to fall over  competitor bags do not do this  because i am using this bag as my mobile professional office these two items alone make it impossible to use the bag  this is disappointing because other features are better than competitors  some items that are better  material construction is better fabric is more durable and most importantly the straps are more comfortable  but in the end the functionality is impaired by the second pocket and the failure to be selfstanding  i am returning the item

prod_name: the north face jester backpack
title: obnoxiously topheavy
review: this is a wellconstructed backpack that feels high quality the padding on the back is great its breathable and very comfortable to wear i liked so much about it but the topheaviness made it a total deal breaker there is one large compartment with a laptoptablet pocket thats very useful however the smaller outer zip pocket only goes halfway down the bag which means that if you put too much in it the bag tips over no matter how you try to lean it against anything it also makes it difficult to access the large compartment also if the zipper on the large compartment is even slightly open when you have a lot of things in the smaller pocket the weight of the small pocket opens up the large compartment resulting in your things spilling all over the place additionally despite having a pocket on either side for water bottles you can only carry one at a time because the pocket on the other side becomes very small when using one pocket id been using this backpack for a few months for school so i cant return but believe me when i say the problems i mentioned here have been a daily irritation which made me really regret buying it
